.TH FOLLOW 1 "2012-04-06"

.SH NAME
.B follow
\(en standalone version of tail -f

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B follow
.I FILENAME

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B follow
is a standalone version of
.BR tail (1)
-f which echoes the whole file before it starts to follow.

It outputs data which was appended to the specified file as the file
grows.  This can, for example, be useful when monitoring log files.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I FILENAME
The filename of the file which should be followed.

